e":"Bill Cusworth","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Directors","individual_id":"019b7b5f-d72e-71e1-9b77-0b5a3942e771","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Terry Farrah","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration","individual_id":"019b8129-1685-7bec-b7d7-0583cbca16a9","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Mark Ellison-Taylor","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Start","individual_id":"019b7fc3-dc9e-7d4d-8f7e-473c5d3e9ac6","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Anna Urbanova","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Start","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7d2b-95da-67b1466bb647","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Jan Urban","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"Older COC Results Website: http://www.old.cascadeoc.org/Results2002/carkeek.html","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"A fine sunny August day for this meet. Although Eric, arriving a tad late with the maps, was hanging controls for course 3 with runners at his heels, and some course 3 runners complained about brambly bits, the meet was a general success.\nIt worked well for us to hold registration at the southeast corner of the park -- parking was fairly easy, and the spot was uncrowded -- though we did shell out $100 for a portable toilet since there were no permanent ones nearby.\nIt was delightful to have guests from Ireland, including Conor Short (M10) and Ruairi Short (M14) who ran very well on courses 1 and 2, and Ruth Lynam who narrowly beat Cascade's Debbie Newell for top women's score on course 3.\n-- Terry Farrah"}
